import bs4 
import requests
import json

def scraper(url: str):
  # send request to url and fetch page contents
  response = requests.get(url)
  
  # parse page contents using BeautifulSoup
  soup = bs4.BeautifulSoup(response.text, 'html.parser')
  
  # find all job postings on the page using the g-title class
  job_postings = soup.find_all('div', {'class': 'g-title'})
  
  # create a list to store job listings
  job_listings = []
  
  # loop through job postings and extract relevant information
  for posting in job_postings:
    # extract title
    title = posting.find('h5', {'data-qa': 'posting-name'}).text
    
    # extract tag
    tag = posting.find('span', {'class': 'display-inline-block small-category-label workplaceTypes'}).text.strip()
    
    # extract apply link
    apply_link = posting.find('a', {'class': 'posting-btn-submit template-btn-submit black'})['href']
    
    # create dictionary to store job data
    job_data = {
      'title': title,
      'tag': tag,
      'apply_link': apply_link
    }
    
    # append job data to job listings list
    job_listings.append(job_data)
    
  # convert job listings list to JSON format
  job_listings = json.dumps(job_listings)
  
  # print job listings
  print(job_listings)
  
if __name__ == '__main__':
  url = "https://jobs.lever.co/appboxo"
  scraper(url)
